  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Offshore Lead Variation Manager",
  "description": "<p>Looking for an experienced Lead Variation Manager to take full ownership and leadership of all contract variation matters.<br /><br />The successful candidate will be responsible for guiding all Contractor projects departments to identify and develop variations and preparing variations support documents, for negotiating with Client and securing client approval for project variations, directly impacting project profitability and risk mitigation. <br /></p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Lead the end-to-end variation process:</strong> From identification and substantiation to submission, negotiation, and final agreement with the client.</li><li><strong>Contractual Expertise:</strong> Provide expert analysis of the EPC contract terms to identify legitimate grounds for variations (change in scope, unforeseen conditions, client-driven changes, etc.).</li><li><strong>Claim Management:</strong> Develop robust, well-documented variation claims and time extension requests, ensuring full compliance with contract procedures.</li><li><strong>Quantification:</strong> Work closely with project controls, engineering, and construction teams to accurately quantify the cost and schedule impact of variations.</li><li><strong>Negotiation:</strong> Serve as the focal point of variation and lead negotiator for all variation-related discussions with the client.</li><li><strong>Reporting:</strong> Prepare regular detailed reports for senior project and company management on the status of all variations, potential exposures, and opportunities.</li><li><strong>Team Leadership:</strong> Guide and mentor other commercial staff on variation management best practices.</li></ul><h3><strong>Essential Qualifications & Experience:</strong></h3><ul><li>Must have a business or variation experience working for international EPC Contractors</li><li>Demonstrable track record of successfully managing variations on large-scale, complex EPC offshore projects in the oil and gas sector</li><li>Those who have project experience with Operators are preferred</li><li>At least 10 years of experience in a similar position</li><li>Experience on at least 3 Offshore/FPSO projects in a similar capacity</li><li>In-depth knowledge of international contract forms (e.g., FIDIC) and bespoke EPC contract structures.</li><li>Exceptional negotiation, communication, and analytical skills. Must be assertive, proactive, and results-driven</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 15,
